          "Two business owners sat down with the exact same AI tool last week. Same tool, same day, same subscription. One of them walked away with a week of work finished in one afternoon. The other one walked away with a paragraph of mush and a fresh opinion about how overhyped all of this is. Same tool. The difference was not the tool. It was not talent either. It was a short list of skills that almost nobody is teaching, because they do not look like AI skills at all. They look old fashioned. Clear thinking. Plain writing. Taste. The nerve to make a decision. I run four businesses, mostly by myself, from a small town in Montana, because AI systems do the heavy lifting. And I am telling you, the skill map has flipped. What is rising is not what you think. And what is falling might be the very thing you built your identity on."
