          "And I want to pause here, because you might be feeling this one in your chest. Maybe you spent ten years getting fast at something a machine now does in seconds. That deserves real grief, not a pep talk. I have had this exact conversation with designers, bookkeepers, and writers, and the ones who come through it fastest are the ones who name the loss out loud instead of pretending it is fine. It is honest to say, I was proud of that, and the ground moved. Let yourself say it. But then notice what actually transfers. The discipline it took to get that good, the eye you developed, the standards you hold. Those ride along to whatever comes next. The syntax was never the treasure. The judgment you built while learning it was.",
